entries.femaleVariant: It worked. I did it.
Johnny, Hanako kept her word.
No, I have changed.
Can ya stop being a dick for just one minute?
I don't buy your rebel-against-the-world bullshit anymore.
Got it all wrong. No way that V would've ever made it this far.
Jesus, can you stop being a prick for just a minute?
Maybe. But that V also couldn't stomach betrayal.
Wait, that's what you think? I betrayed you?
Seen plenty o' Johnny Silverhand by now, and you know what?
The whole pissed-at-the-world rebel warrior front you got goin'? Yeah, not fallin' for it anymore.
entries.maleVariant: The whole pissed-at-the-world rebel warrior front you got goin'? Not fallin' for it anymore.

entries.femaleVariant: Just wanted to talk. For old time's sake.
Wanna part on good terms. As friends.
Wanna explain everything.
You? Me? There's nothing left to say.
Just wanted to talk. One last time. For old time's sake.
Wanna part ways on good terms, Johnny. As friends.
Want you to hear me out, lemme explain all this.
I'm listenin'.
[Stand] That was the deal.
Explain? Oh. Then talk.
You an' me? Don't think we have anything left to say.
This is it, Johnny. I just came to say goodbye, that's all.
Listen... I'm on an operating table gettin' sliced open. Arasaka docs are takin' the chip out as we speak.
I mean, you knew it'd end this way…
That the day would come when I'd want to be normal again, want my life back.
"Normal" is overrated… if it exists at all. They're cuttin' a piece of us out, and that'll leave a hole. Forever.
[Stand] What choice did I have?
[Stand] There is no "us!"
That was the deal we made. I'd stay – you'd go.
What choice did I have?
No such thing as "us"! I am V. You are Johnny Silverhand. Hell, you're a fucking construct!
entries.maleVariant: No such thing as "us"! I am V! You are Johnny Silverhand. Hell, you're a fucking CONSTRUCT!

entries.femaleVariant: Stay true to yourself? Give a thought to a tiny concept called loyalty?
Deal was to fight side by side, have each other's backs.
Then what's it about?
No, it's you who doesn't get it.
Gonna deny who you are, ignore who you've become?
If you're all paranoid about being thrown in another Arasaka prison, don't be – they're gonna shred you.
You're never gonna get it. It's not about Arasaka. Not even about life and death.
Then what's it all about, Johnny? Enlighten me.
No, it's you who doesn't understand.
Conversation's pointless... G'bye, Johnny.
Always been lost. And if anyone near you had their shit figured out, you couldn't stand it.
Alt, Rogue, Kerry – all of 'em.
Different times. I've changed.
Dirty bomb, destructive Johnny. Bringing everyone and everything around him to ruin in the name of his death wish.
entries.maleVariant: Dirty bomb, destructive Johnny. Bringing everyone and everything around to ruin in the name of his death wish.

entries.femaleVariant: Not about to be your next victim. I've got a life to live.
The principle, V. It's always about the principle.
Swap meat for chrome, live a BD fantasy, whatever – but at the end of it all, it's the code you live by that defines who you are.
Ever get lost, it shows you the way home.
Bust up into pieces, it puts you back together again.
That Rockerboy Silverhand's credo, words he lived by?
Sure, yeah – but what's it worth?
Goodbye, Johnny.
See ya 'round, Johnny. Thanks for everything.
Get the fuck outta my life.
I don't wanna drag this out. Just… see ya around, Johnny. And thanks. For everything.
Conversation's pointless. Just get the fuck outta my life.
Sorry, no mute button on your conscience. A part of me'll always be with you. Always.
It's been a real ride, Johnny. Not one I'll regret, but not one I'll miss, either.
entries.maleVariant: It has been a real ride, Johnny. Not one I'll regret, but not one I'll miss, either.

entries.femaleVariant: Oh, you'll regret it. Lose a friend and you always regret it.
'Member Jackie's last words? About the chip? "Hold on to it, V. For me."
Yeah... Guess not.
We've come to the end. Came to say goodbye.
'Member what Dex asked you? "Quiet life or blaze of glory?"
Sure, I remember.
Shame you chose wrong. Damn shame.
If not for you, I'd be long dead. Several times over.
Lookin' at you now – reminds me of the moment we met.
Still see that same small-time merc, little thief with her head in the clouds. Haven't changed a bit.
entries.maleVariant: Still see that same small-time merc, little thief with his head in the clouds. Haven't changed a bit.

entries.femaleVariant: Just… wouldn't've survived. I had to grow stronger. And I did.
Worse. Lots. You betrayed yourself.
Y'know... you remind me of someone.
The Johnny of yore never gave a shit about anyone. Betrayal came easy, was somethin' to brag about.
Wait, that's what you think? I betrayed you?
Worse. Lots. You betrayed yourself.
Uncanny. Here I stand lookin' at an old pic of myself back in the day.
Rogue, Alt, others... abandoned 'em all. And now here's you, abandoning me, abandoning yourself.
[Sit] You got no right to judge me.
[Sit] The hell do you mean by that?
Got no right to judge me.
Couldn't be more wrong. Biochip did more'n just blend our memories.
That line that kept V and Silverhand separate, well, faded a while back.
The hell you mean by that?
How's that give you the right to talk down to me?
I'm the V who mourns our pal Jackie, the V who's fuckin' livid at Brigitte. I'm the V with a heavy conscience.
Biochip did more'n just blend our memories.
And you? Who are you?
I'm still here. I know what I want, and I know where I came from.
That line that kept V and Silverhand separate, well, faded a while back.
I, I, I. Who's this "I"? You even know?
Same old V who died in a landfill.
The V who chose to survive.
I'm bitter. And sad. Guess that's who I am now.
Same V who was left to die in that landfill. Nothin's changed.
I'm the V who chose to live.
I... I dunno. Get a little lost when I look inside.
Did what I set out to do. I'm the winner, here.
Don't know who I am.
I know I'm not lookin' in the rearview.
Dunno who I am anymore.
And your will to fight? To tell Death to go fuck himself? Where's that come from?
Always had that. That's who I am.
How can you be so sure? I mean, when you reach back, how can you be sure whose memories you're dippin' into?
Same drive that kept Silverhand goin' his whole life.
That drive and two thoughts – never look back, never look to those around you.
Just keep movin', look ahead, stare Death straight in the eye.
You're not the only rebel around here.
And I'm not the only one to have missed the bigger picture.
I'm stronger than ever. But I... I can't seem to keep my mind straight.
entries.maleVariant: I'm stronger than ever, but I... I can't seem to keep my mind straight.

entries.femaleVariant: How do you feel?
Bitter, I guess. And sad.
And disappointed. I know.
I'm stronger than I've ever been. I won my goddamn life back.
You sure talk the talk, but I know better. Feel the same way you do.
I don't give a fuck what you think you know!
Now that sounds like a Silverhand original.
We're a tangled web, you and me – one and the same.
So if you're here to tell me somethin', it's 'cause you need to hear it yourself.
Not sure that's possible anymore.
And we did that. We won.
Better to die on your feet than live on your knees.
Sold a piece of your soul to the devil. YOU are no longer all there. YOU are not YOU.
Somethin' Johnny picked up from V – the old V.
You sold a part of yourself, of us, to a megacorp. Was it really worth it?
Guess not everybody gets their last wish.
[Stand] There you go, blaming Arasaka again.
Things didn't go as Johnny planned, wanted. So Johnny needs someone to blame.
And pinning every little thing on Arasaka got old a long, long time ago.
Arasaka's got nothing to do with this. This is about trust. About who you're turning into.
[Touch Johnny] Hanako kept her word.
What're you waiting for?
Fucking pathetic.
That seriously what you wanted?
Oh, V...
Jesus, V.
Ohhh, V...
